          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "Looks good overall, couple of minor comments / questions below",
          "createdAt": "2026-06-04T14:13:12Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-06-04T14:31:04Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 32,
              "body": "Note that this seems to be the first place where \"split model\" is mentioned in the document. Might be worth putting a reference to the next section.",
              "createdAt": "2026-06-04T14:13:12Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-06-04T14:31:04Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 34,
              "body": "I wonder if we want to be a bit more loose here with the wording. Currently it sounds as if the PAT only covers the lowest layer of attestation (the hardware), but I think we'd better make it about the state of the whole TCB. In CCA, for example, there's a platform token, a realm token, and now a key token.\n\nThoughts?",
              "createdAt": "2026-06-04T14:20:09Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-06-04T14:31:04Z"
            }
